{"questionId":"22115234","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The total length of the roads is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>33</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <strong>two</strong> expressions, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, for the shortest distance required to walk along all of the paths, beginning and ending at the same vertex.</p>\n<p>Include in your answer the interval of values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which each expression is valid.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct intervals seen <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>or</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">AND</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>or</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The case of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math> must be included for this <em><strong>A1</strong></em> to be awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to add edges to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>33</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>5</mn></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>5</mn></math>) then repeat <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math> and) length is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>33</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>5</mn></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>5</mn></math>) then repeat <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi></math> and) length is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>33</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>38</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If the intervals are not explicit, award at most <em><strong>A0(M1)A1A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22115234","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find two expressions, in terms of x, for the shortest distance required to walk along all of the paths, beginning and ending at the same vertex. Include in your answer the interval","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Graph theory","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Tree and cycle algorithms, Chinese postman, travelling salesman"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}